## Root Cause Analysis

The build failed because `%autosetup` does not support the `-q` (quiet) option. Unlike `%setup`, `%autosetup` is quiet by default, so adding `-q` causes an "Unknown option" error:

```
autosetup: invalid option -- 'q'
>>> [   12s] error: /home/abuild/rpmbuild/SOURCES/oterm.spec: line 54: Unknown option q in autosetup(a:b:cCDn:TvNS:p:)
```

The previous attempt tried to fix `%setup -q` by converting to `%autosetup`, but mistakenly kept the `-q` flag.

## Fix

Remove the `-q` flag from `%autosetup`:

```spec
%prep
-%autosetup -q -n oterm-%{version}
+%autosetup -n oterm-%{version}
```

## Additional Notes

Since this is a Python package using `pyproject.toml` with `%pyproject_wheel` and `%pyproject_install`, ensure the spec file has these BuildRequires if missing:

```spec
BuildRequires:  python-rpm-macros
BuildRequires:  python3-setuptools
```
